CARLETON DRY GOODS CO. v. ROGERS. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 17, 1903.) No. 1,193. Appeal from the District Court of the United States for the Northern District of Texas.

Before PARDEE and SHELBY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

We find nothing in the reasons presented for a rehearing to make us doubt the correctness of the decision heretofore rendered (120 Fed. 14), and the rehearing is denied.
